race.description: Sdra Evergreen Turf Country Champs Preview Hcp (C4)
race.comment: Good field engaged for the Country Champs preview. BON HOLLER (8) resumes and is a promising type. Trialled well in readiness at Albury and can launch into this campaign with a win. Seib holds a strong hand. MASTER OF DISGUISE (2) drops back into a much more suitable assignment after a disappointing effort at the Gold Coast. Kept fresh with 30 days and has the hot-hand hoop in Boudvillain reunited. Will push forward from the favourable draw and give a bold sight. Stablemate GHOST WALKER (5) returns and has been readied with a solid hitout at Canberra. The form Around him last prep stacks right up and he boasts a strong record here. No reason he can't land the winning blow fresh. TOOMPINE (3) continues to leave himself with too much to do but possesses a strong turn of foot. Will appreciate the hot tempo and can cause a late scare on the quick back-up.
